The paper discusses a technique for preventing code reuse attacks using deep learning, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of deep learning for control flow integrity checking suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions issues related to modifying binaries and compilers, which suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the technique involves splitting the control flow graph into chains, which suggests a focus on programming languages (cs.PL).
